Package net.sf.javaml.clustering

Provides algorithms to cluster data.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Clusterer A common interface for all clustering techniques.
 

Class Summary
AQBC This class implements the Adaptive Quality-based Clustering Algorithm, based on the implementation in MATLAB by De Smet et al., ESAT - SCD (SISTA), K.U.Leuven, Belgium.
Cobweb Class implementing the Cobweb and Classit clustering algorithms.

Note: the application of node operators (merging, splitting etc.) in terms of ordering and priority differs (and is somewhat ambiguous) between the original Cobweb and Classit papers.
DensityBasedSpatialClustering Provides the density-based-spatial-scanning clustering algorithm.
FarthestFirst Cluster data using the FarthestFirst algorithm.

For more information see:

Hochbaum, Shmoys (1985).
IterativeFarthestFirst XXX DOC
IterativeKMeans This class implements an extension of KMeans.
IterativeMultiKMeans This class implements an extension of KMeans, combining Iterative- en MultiKMeans.
KMeans Implements the K-means algorithms as described by Mac Queen in 1967.
KMedoids Implementation of the K-medoids algorithm.
MultiKMeans This class implements an extension of KMeans (SKM).
OPTICS Mihael Ankerst, Markus M.
SOM An implementation of the Self Organizing Maps algorithm as proposed by Kohonen.
 

Enum Summary
SOM.GridType Enumeration of all grid types that are supported in a self organizing map.
SOM.LearningType  
SOM.NeighbourhoodFunction
